The '''Atlantic Ocean''' is the second-largest [[ocean]], covering approximately one-fifth of the [[Earth]]'s surface. The ocean's name, derived from [[Greek mythology]], means the "[[Sea]] of [[Atlas (mythology)|Atlas]]." The oldest known mention of this [[name]] is contained in ''[[Histories (Herodotus)|The Histories]]'' of [[Herodotus]] around 450 BC (I 202). The Atlantic is famous for many different historic events, one of them being the sinking of the [[RMS Titanic]] on [[April 14]], [[1912]] after hitting an [[iceberg]].



